SIMPLE: deceitfulness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deceitfulness
<hw>De*ceit"ful*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
disposition to deceive; <as>as, a man's <ex>deceitfulness</ex> may be
habitual</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being deceitful; <as>as, the
<ex>deceitfulness</ex> of a man's practices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tendency to mislead or deceive.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>deceitfulness</xex> of riches.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Matt. xiii.
22.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deceitless</ent>⟦br⟧
